  "market_context": "NASDAQ 100 E-mini Futures on the 1-minute chart. Price displaced upward without first sweeping a prior low, then dropped lower, moved below a consolidation range and aggressively rallied back into it, forming a deviation/box setup structure.",
  "key_observation": "Although a box setup formed with a clean deviation from the range (accumulation, manipulation, distribution), the prior displacement up did not originate from a lower time frame liquidity sweep, making the structure shift invalid by the analyst's checklist.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Noted price went a tick below a prior low but discounted it as insufficient as a stop raid.",
    "Observed an aggressive displacement upward but rejected it as a valid structure shift because no liquidity sweep preceded it.",
    "Tracked price dropping lower, then breaking below the consolidation range and aggressively returning back into the range — identifying this as the deviation from the range.",
    "Framed the sequence as accumulation, manipulation, distribution and anticipated a retest of the manipulation before price reaches for the opposite side of the range.",
    "Watched candles fail to close below the old low, confirmed move higher, took partials toward resting buy-side liquidity above.",
    "Acknowledged that this trade triggered as a box setup entry but emphasized it lacked the required lower time frame liquidity sweep prior to displacement."
  ],
  "outcome": "Box setup played out higher into resting liquidity above; analyst notes partials were taken, but stresses he would not personally take this entry without a prior liquidity sweep.",
  "lessons": "A box setup can still resolve correctly via AMD, but without a lower time frame liquidity sweep preceding the displacement, the setup does not meet the checklist criteria and should be skipped.",
